Description:
This award is for the purchase of the Varonis data classification and security tool for a three year term. This subscription includes:

DatAdvantage for Windows Onprem subscription for 650 Users for 36 Months;
Data Classification Framework for Windows and SharePoint Onprem
subscription for 650 Users;
Data Classification Policy Pack On-prem subscription for 650 Users for 36 Months;
1 Collector On-prem subscription for 36 Months;
DatAlert Suite On-prem subscription for 650 Users for 36 Months;
Automation Engine On-prem subscription for 650 Users for 36 Months;
7 Professional Services Engagement (1 day).

This award was undertaken via a Call off from a Framework Agreement and the award will be to Insight Direct UK Ltd.

The Ministry of Defence (MOD) were inviting bids for the provision of numerous Commercial Off-the-Shelf (COT) licence renewals and support and maintenance. 
The Authority have numerous COT applications on their corporate system which required licence upgrades and maintenance. These applications include: 
ZoomText; 
Paintshop Pro; 
JAW's; 
ClaroView and; 
Read & Write Gold. 
The Authority required support and maintenance for the licences outlined above and Potential Providers were asked to submit support and maintenance prices for both a one (1) and three (3) year term.
